d887598c-b3b3-5c05-a657-20f4c8f38c3d,tg:rubgr:1575,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"

[recto] Ad [Addendum] 33. Ad Cripples Louvre. Witt Library. Maerten van Cleve. Cripples with foxtails: 1) Farkashazy Sale, [onleesbaar] Budapest without bishop's mitre, 21 April, 1927, N° 78, Holz 73 x106 = Gudlaugsson III?[sic] Not the same (2 looks better than 1. Here 3rd man has not a bishop's mitre); 2) Stroganoff Sale, Lepke Berlin, 12-13 May 1931, N° 22. = Gudlaugsson I. Faschings treiben auf dem Markte - Vorn drei Bettlerkrüppel, die weiste Rössche mit Fuchsschwänzen benäht. Holz, 75 x 106 cm. Monogrammiert u[nd] datiert 1579, Wurzbach I, p. 292; Thieme-Becker, VII, p. 100; one of them has a proper bishop's mitre; [verso] 3) with bishop's mitre [...]; B) Verwante Komposition [...]; C) Drawing Albertina, Benesch N° 90 [...]
